Scottish private schools maintain a track record of academic excellence, and this was continued in 2018 with outstanding exam results, which are further strengthened by each student and collective success in sports, the arts, music as well as hard work.
With over 30,000 students across Scotland, these schools, represented by the Scottish Board of Private Schools (SCIS) strive to provide the best services for students and parents.
The independent school aims to prepare its students for further and higher education, their chosen career, and their role as world citizens.
As an education sector that can design and implement a school curriculum as expected, we see modern languages continue to be popular and desirable elective subjects in many schools.
Nelson Mandela said, “If you talk to someone in a language he understands, your speech will go to his head.
