Having multilingual skills, especially the language of countries with a developing economy, will equip children with better opportunities to find meaningful jobs.
In Scotland, each school will teach a different language.
Some schools will focus on more classic modern languages, while others will teach the languages considered most important in English for the next few years, namely 2020, such as Mandarin or Japanese.
Whatever your child’s interests, there will always be a number of languages to choose from in independent schools, with teaching staff who are experts in this field.
Scotland's independent schools are aimed at providing a learning environment that will prepare children and equip them with the skills necessary to succeed, no matter what happens in the future.
